comments.body:
> ReserveSELinuxLabels() s a public API, and I'm not particularly enthusiastic about breaking those in general. Does libpod still need to start calling it?

I chose to remove (rather than deprecate) it because:
 - there are no existing (open source) users (according to [this](https://sourcegraph.com/search?q=ReserveSELinuxLabels&patternType=keyword&sm=0&df=%5B%22file%22%2C%22Exclude+vendor%22%2C%22-file%3A%28%5E%7C%2F%29vendor%2F%22%5D&__cc=1));
 - it was made public to be used by podman in Sep 2018 (see commit d0846b1, PR #1041) but I
was not able to find any traces of it being ever used in podman;
 - its internal usage was removed in Oct 2018 (see commit 1eaaf790, PR #1102);
 - bumping selinux requires changes in this code, which seems to be unused for 5+ years.
